{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.18",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 18,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 18 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:1",
      "text": "I will love thee, O Lord, my strength.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:2",
      "text": "The Lord is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my buckler, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:3",
      "text": "I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised: so shall I be saved from mine enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:4",
      "text": "The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:5",
      "text": "The sorrows of hell compassed me about: the snares of death prevented me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:6",
      "text": "In my distress I called upon the Lord, and cried unto my God: he heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him, even into his ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:7",
      "text": "Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken, because he was wroth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:8",
      "text": "There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:9",
      "text": "He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness was under his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:10",
      "text": "And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly: yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:11",
      "text": "He made darkness his secret place; his pavilion round about him were dark waters and thick clouds of the skies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:12",
      "text": "At the brightness that was before him his thick clouds passed, hail stones and coals of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:13",
      "text": "The Lord also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail stones and coals of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:14",
      "text": "Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings, and discomfited them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:15",
      "text": "Then the channels of waters were seen, and the foundations of the world were discovered at thy rebuke, O Lord, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:16",
      "text": "He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:17",
      "text": "He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:18",
      "text": "They prevented me in the day of my calamity: but the Lord was my stay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:19",
      "text": "He brought me forth also into a large place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:20",
      "text": "The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:21",
      "text": "For I have kept the ways of the Lord, and have not wickedly departed from my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:22",
      "text": "For all his judgments were before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:23",
      "text": "I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:24",
      "text": "Therefore hath the Lord recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:25",
      "text": "With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful; with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:26",
      "text": "With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself froward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:27",
      "text": "For thou wilt save the afflicted people; but wilt bring down high looks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:28",
      "text": "For thou wilt light my candle: the Lord my God will enlighten my darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:29",
      "text": "For by thee I have run through a troop; and by my God have I leaped over a wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:30",
      "text": "As for God, his way is perfect: the word of the Lord is tried: he is a buckler to all those that trust in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:31",
      "text": "For who is God save the Lord? or who is a rock save our God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:32",
      "text": "It is God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:33",
      "text": "He maketh my feet like hinds’ feet, and setteth me upon my high places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:34",
      "text": "He teacheth my hands to war, so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:35",
      "text": "Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation: and thy right hand hath holden me up, and thy gentleness hath made me great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:36",
      "text": "Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:37",
      "text": "I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:38",
      "text": "I have wounded them that they were not able to rise: they are fallen under my feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:39",
      "text": "For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle: thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:40",
      "text": "Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:41",
      "text": "They cried, but there was none to save them: even unto the Lord, but he answered them not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.42",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:42",
      "text": "Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.43",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:43",
      "text": "Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people; and thou hast made me the head of the heathen: a people whom I have not known shall serve me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.44",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:44",
      "text": "As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.45",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:45",
      "text": "The strangers shall fade away, and be afraid out of their close places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.46",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:46",
      "text": "The Lord liveth; and blessed be my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.47",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:47",
      "text": "It is God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.48",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:48",
      "text": "He delivereth me from mine enemies: yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.49",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:49",
      "text": "Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O Lord, among the heathen, and sing praises unto thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.18.50",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 18,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 18:50",
      "text": "Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
